{
  "_comment": "Gemma 4 12B dense HF→engine tensor name map. The pattern is the same as gemma4_moe/name_mapping.json — swap 'model.language_model' → 'language_model.model' (MLX-LM convention). Vision/audio tensors are KEPT (not skipped) because in Gemma 4 the multimodal projections are JUST matrices (single matmul for audio, patch_dense + pos_embedding + 2 LNs for vision) — no separate transformer encoder. Drop the 'model.' prefix for those: 'model.vision_embedder.X' → 'vision_embedder.X', etc.",

  "_comment_v_proj": "v_proj.weight is only present on the 40 sliding-attention layers. The 8 full-attention layers (every 6th: 5, 11, 17, 23, 29, 35, 41, 47) reuse K as V — attention_k_eq_v=true. The {L} expansion creates entries for all 48 layers but lookups for non-existent ones are harmless (load_name_mapping just builds the lookup table; classify only ever sees tensors that actually exist in the safetensors).",

  "model.language_model.embed_tokens.weight": "language_model.model.embed_tokens.weight",
  "model.language_model.norm.weight":         "language_model.model.norm.weight",

